\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
1.
 Purpose
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The purpose of this policy is to establish the mandatory security controls for the protection,
 access,
 transport,
 and verifiable sanitization of all physical and digital media storing Elko County information.
 This policy prevents the unauthorized disclosure of Confidential and Restricted data,
 including Criminal Justice Information (CJI),
 by enforcing strict lifecycle constraints from media provisioning through destruction,
 consistent with FBI CJIS Security Policy Version 6.0 and NIST SP 800-88 Revision 1.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
2.
 Scope
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy applies to all Elko County Information Operations personnel,
 County employees,
 contractors,
 and third-party vendors who access,
 transport,
 store,
 or sanitize County media.
 Covered media includes,
 but is not limited to,
 portable storage devices (e.g.,
 USB drives,
 external hard drives),
 optical media,
 magnetic tapes,
 solid-state drives,
 internal hard drives within multifunction printers/copiers (MFPs),
 networking equipment NVRAM,
 and physical/printed media containing County data.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
3.
 Roles and Responsibilities
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
IT Director
\series default
:
 Shall serve as the Technical Authority governing media sanitization standards.
 Shall act as the Local Agency Security Officer (LASO) and approve all sanitization methods and exceptions involving Criminal Justice Information (CJI).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Information Operations Personnel (Administrators and Support Specialists)
\series default
:
 Shall execute required media sanitization procedures prior to the disposal,
 transfer,
 or reuse of IT assets.
 Shall verify sanitization effectiveness and maintain the Configuration Management Database (CMDB) and logging records for all sanitized media.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Department Heads (Data Owners)
\series default
:
 Shall enforce physical media protection and ensure physical documents generated within their departments are destroyed in accordance with this policy and assigned data classification levels.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
All Personnel
\series default
:
 Shall physically protect County media in their custody from unauthorized access,
 loss,
 or theft,
 and shall report any loss or suspected compromise of media immediately.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
4.
 Compliance and Exceptions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Adherence to this policy is mandatory.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Enforcement
\series default
:
 The unauthorized disposal of media or the use of unsanctioned portable storage devices shall result in immediate asset confiscation,
 access revocation,
 and corrective action defined under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
CJIS Reporting Requirement
\series default
:
 Personnel shall report the loss or theft of any media containing CJI to the IT Director (LASO) immediately,
 and no later than one (1) hour after discovery.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Records Retention
\series default
:
 Information Operations shall retain Certificates of Destruction and sanitization logs in accordance with the applicable Nevada Local Government Records Retention Schedules.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Exceptions
\series default
:
 Exceptions shall be documented within a formal Risk Acceptance Memo signed by the IT Director,
 containing specified compensating controls and a defined expiration date.
 Exceptions involving CJI shall require explicit written approval from the CJIS Systems Officer (CSO) prior to implementation.
\end_layout

